docs.abstract: The number of publicly out athletes in men’s biggest pro leagues lags far behind that in women’s sports. Will Carl Nassib’s announcement change that?
docs.snippet: The number of publicly out athletes in men’s biggest pro leagues lags far behind that in women’s sports. Will Carl Nassib’s announcement change that?
docs.lead_paragraph: Congratulatory posts flooded social media on Monday when Las Vegas Raiders defensive lineman Carl Nassib announced on Instagram that he is gay, becoming the first active N.F.L. player to do so.

headline.main: A Gay N.F.L. Player Broke a Barrier. Will Other L.G.B.T.Q. Athletes Follow?

docs.abstract: From the Williamstown Theater Festival to New York Stage and Film, theatergoers can experience world premieres, concerts and more.
docs.snippet: From the Williamstown Theater Festival to New York Stage and Film, theatergoers can experience world premieres, concerts and more.
docs.lead_paragraph: Most summers, as tourists pour into New York City to see theater, New Yorkers pour out to see theater elsewhere. This summer, though, they may do so with extra ardor. As the pandemic lifts, the pent-up demand for live, in-person theater is first being met in the Berkshires and in the mid-Hudson region, where companies are putting up tents, arranging outdoor immersive experiences and welcoming audiences to buildings that have been empty for too long.

headline.main: A Guide to Theater Festivals in New York and the Berkshires
headline.print_headline: Finally, Theater Options Abound Once More

docs.abstract: One of the most dominant players in tennis history, Navratilova was a cultural pioneer when the world wasn’t prepared for an outspoken lesbian. Finally, the world is catching up, and she’s still here.
docs.snippet: One of the most dominant players in tennis history, Navratilova was a cultural pioneer when the world wasn’t prepared for an outspoken lesbian. Finally, the world is catching up, and she’s still here.
docs.lead_paragraph: FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. — Martina Navratilova sat at a dockside restaurant in Florida this spring, wearing worn-out jeans, a denim button-down shirt that hung loosely at her waist and a 1619 cap that one of her five dogs had gnawed on. It’s her favorite hat these days.

headline.main: Martina Navratilova Has Plenty to Say
headline.print_headline: Still a Pioneer at 64,  Navratilova Has  Plenty on Her Mind

docs.abstract: M.L.B. is still working to incorporate Negro league statistics, but a popular website now lets fans put some of the numbers in context.
docs.snippet: M.L.B. is still working to incorporate Negro league statistics, but a popular website now lets fans put some of the numbers in context.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Monday, Baseball Reference, the go-to source on the internet for such matters, would have told you that Stan Musial led the major leagues with a .357 batting average in 1943. It also would have said numerous pitchers took a turn leading the majors in strikeouts per nine innings between 1927 and 1945, and that the top three batters in career adjusted on-base-plus-slugging percentage were Babe Ruth, Ted Williams and Barry Bonds.

headline.main: Baseball Reference Adds Negro Leagues Statistics, Rewriting Its Record Book
headline.print_headline: Go-To Statistics Source Adds Negro Leagues

docs.lead_paragraph: A statue of George Floyd that was installed in Brooklyn less than a week ago was spray-painted and marked with a white supremacist group’s logo in an act of vandalism that the police were investigating as a hate crime, officials said on Thursday.

docs.abstract: Black candidates are leading in this New York City election. Can they avoid the pitfalls?
docs.snippet: Black candidates are leading in this New York City election. Can they avoid the pitfalls?
docs.lead_paragraph: New York City — the nation’s largest city — held its widely watched primaries for city officials on Tuesday. It is broadly believed that whoever wins the Democratic primary in this heavily Democratic city will win the general election.
